Width of plots can be specified in LaTeX document

Modified the template using some pgfkeys magic to check for the existence
of the /artist/width key.  If it exists, use its value to define the width
of the plot.  If it doesn't, use the value specified in the python source.

In effect, the width of the plot can be chosen at the time of creation of
the plot (in python), but can be overridden at the time of publication (in
LaTeX).

Added methods to add a label to a plot

You can specify in which corner of the plot the label should be placed, as

Plot marks overlap intelligently

Unfilled plot marks visually overlap each other.  They are transparent,
and none eclipses another.  However, they *do* eclipse any line.  In that
case, they seem to be filled with white.  Overlapping plot marks on top of
a line eclipse the line, but not each other.

This is accomplished by adding two series to plot_series_list.  The first
one draws empty (white) plot marks, and only then are unfilled marks
drawn.

Perform all background clear operations first

Otherwise, subsequent plot series erase previously plotted marks.
